The parchment system is flawed horribly. Has been since it's inception. For those players who dont have access to the high end zones where myth has it they drop like candy we are forced to sit it out and wait for them to appear in bazaar for prices that people would be outraged to pay for a fungi tunic.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Actually, I think it's working pretty much as designed, and it's working fairly well.  If you CAN access the high level zones, you'll get your spells first.  When you and your group have acquired the spells, then they'll go to the market.  Like any new item on the market in EQ, the prices are intially high, but eventually come down when supply begins to exceed demand.<br>
<br>
So, you can get into the plains early and get your spells and get to sell the excess for big money, or you can wait and get them later, either by going yourself or gathering the Platinum to pay for those that got there before you, or you can wait even more until the spell prices come down.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I'm a 62 cleric who recently got flagged for POS and POV and COD, and for ALL of those, it just took a single group. If you don't have a group of friends or can't find a gorup at 60+, then you're not playing the game that Verant designed and Sony runs... a MULTIPLAYER online game.<br>
<br>
FYI - I'm here because I have a 50+ mage too.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p>Belhaven<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
