<br>
2 new pets<br>
2 pet weapons<br>
new pet utility<br>
new self buffs (base, regen, resist)<br>
new pet buff<br>
new fire nuke<br>
new rain<br>
new focus items<br>
new damage shield<br>
<br>
The only thing of note is that 61/62 lacks an upgraded magic dd.<br>
<br>
Once you hit 63/64/65 you start hitting spells that actually DEFINE higher capablilty mages. You get upgrades to nearly all these lines, and new utility, all which help define the higher capability mage.<br>
<br>
So (with the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>possible</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> exception of magic dd), the parchment system is working very well. If your'e a casual mage, you have a very good chance at getting all of those &quot;base&quot; spells. More advanced mages get thiers upgrades to these base spells. This adds more definition across mages, instead of everyone always having all spells and being the same. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=38898">Salash Penumbra</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower">Summoner</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.midnightfury.org">Armies</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->!</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells>Spells</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM GAMES AD SCRIPT -->
